5:
That was a very enlightening
conversation. Thank you for your
time.
9:
Hehe, the pleasure was all mine! I'm
just glad to be of service.
13:
You have my utmost respect. Magia
Fest was extremely successful in its
goal of bridging the gap between
cultures.
17:
Understanding such events are key
to realizing the dream which was
passed on to me.
24:
Sorry, but we need you to come with
us!
29:
We've just received word from
Sarliha.
31:
It appears some new remnants of
the Titan were discovered in the
desert!
36:
It is as if we have stepped into a
tomb...
40:
Rakisha and the others found a
cipher inside some documents that
were left behind—'nother parting gift
from Rolan.
42:
We've also found a bunch of World
Flippers. Apparently there's a
buncha these ruins that's been
hidden away.
46:
But this is the only one containing
the remains of the Titan. Its hull is all
but completely destroyed.
51:
The core of the Titan still appears to
be active.
55:
...I will attempt to establish a
connection.
59: You sure that's a good idea?
63:
We have no choice. We cannot
allow such terrible power to fall into
the hands of the kingdom.
77:
We are... the chosen proxy. We...
shall crush... the stars.
78: Mortals... what do you... wish for?
82:
What we desire cannot be granted
to us by false gods.
95:
I am all right. But the connection
must not be severed!
98:
Heed my words! I shall never
become like you...
101:
...I shall never become a killing
machine!
110:
I apologize for causing you concern.
Now that the core has been
subjugated, everything is under
control.
112:
My systems will require
recalibration, but there is no threat
of immediate danger.
120:
Please forgive me for the trouble I
caused you, Sarliha. You even
provided me with these fine new
garments...
125:
Allow me to do at least that much!
They suit you quite well, if I do say so
myself!
140:
Everyone, be on your guard. I have
detected a threat in the vicinity.
144:
An attack... by the kingdom outside
of the gates!
147:
Hey, watch the goods! If we don't
fetch a proper price for 'em, the
difference is comin' outta YOUR cut!
156: Now is your chance! Flee at once!
159:
Get outta our way, you cube-floatin'
freak!
162:
If you do not intend to surrender,
then you leave me no choice.
176:
It appears I need to recalibrate my
attack output as soon as possible.
182:
With that kind of power... we could
reduce the kingdom to rubble in an
instant.
190:
If we take down the kingdom, we
free the borderlands.
195:
But we recovered the Titan's core in
order to prevent such acts of
massacre. We must avoid needless
bloodshed.
202:
Fine. Hold onto that power then. Alk
will need your strength in the battles
to come.
204:
But let me make one thing crystal
clear—you are no longer to
intervene in the affairs of the
borderlands.
208: What do you mean by that?
212:
I've told you before. Power like yours
is intoxicating to those who have
none.
214:
The people of the borderlands are
helpless and desperate—your
presence here would only spark
more conflict.
218:
I cannot deny that possibility. But
my mission here still remains... I
have not yet found the answers I
seek!
222:
Step foot in these lands again, and it
will be the last thing you ever do.
